rComments:
Interesting prof, he and his TAs did a good job of teaching the material. Just wish the exams had more room for making tiny errors - you need to aim for perfection every exam and can't afford to lose marks because of how little marks each test is worth. 

Lectures were fun! Put in work, and stay on top of lectures and you too can get an A.
nice and good
This is a pretty hard class conceptually but the exams were really fair and he gives good lectures. He also really cares about the students' understanding and is helpful when you ask questions.

Very interesting course taught by a very interesting man. I definitely suggest reviewing concepts beforehand to fully appreciate the proofs and problem solving he does during the lectures. Overall, great guy; would recommend.
His lectures are very confusing.
Hard class, decent at explaining things tho.
Smart guy. Has no clue how to teach though.

Prof Salmasian is the best professor for this course. His tests reflect the lectures. If you figure out what the big questions will be, then you're set. The class was incredibly easy for someone who dislikes math. He posted recorded lectures. Most of the time, he finished his lectures in 40-60 minutes. The true and false questions sucked!
This prof does not care to explain and skips most of the fundamental steps in his solutions. The lecture notes are non intuitive and go from 0-100 quick.
Goes way too fast, does not care to explain basic concepts. Unlucky
Very good at explaining the material, would recommend him

This professor explains well the material and lecutres only based on his slides. He doesn't use a book, which is awesome, normally only has 3 or 2 midterms and a final. As long as you read the slides and do the old exams he posts you'll be fine, his exams never change format. Also it's easy to ask him questions be it in class or by email.
easy mid terms the final was tough but overall good class

Exams were hard, not necessarily because of the content, but because you lose extra marks if you get a question wrong. Need to study a lot in this course, but the lectures were pretty clear if you paid attention. Gives you the chance to replace your worst midterm mark if you did better on the final exam. Posts old exams so you know what to expect.
Man doesn't care about students at all and has ridiculously hard midterms and exams. Definitely do not recommend him!!!

Good professor at explaining concepts but his midterms and exams are very difficult.  Goes quite fast and often the T/F will kill you (You lose marks if you get it wrong) however I believe all profs do that T/F format

He is a great teacher, but his midterms are some of the worst I have written so far. Just beware that he marks very hard, so If you mess up one part of an equation you'll lose almost all the marks. Oh, and he subtracts marks for incorrect answers on midterms out of 20. 20 marks means every mark you lose is nearly an entire percentage of your grade.

He teaches directly off of his slides, but he is very good at explaining if you are paying attention. Exams and midterms are reasonable and cover everything he covers in class. There are no surprises and he even posts the last 10 years of previous midterms and exams so you can know what to expect on the midterms
Awful teaching style. Midterms are wayyyy too difficult than other sections. You won't survive in his class
Nice prof! He is really good at explaining, and the scanned lecture notes are helpful. His final was easy, but the midterm was so hard

His teaches strictly off his slides so missing a couple classes won't be a problem. I think that he'd be a better prof if he actually took us step-by-step to solve problems (maybe by writing more on the board). His tests are hard because of true and  false, he takes marks off when you choose it wrong :( overall, decent prof, not too bad.
Exam are so hard.
Thanks to his awful teaching style I'm failing this class
Terrible prof, doesn't know what he's doing. Exams were ridiculously hard! i don't recommend taking his class!
His slides seem alright but once you do the practice exam you realize how little you have learned in his class and how you are going to fail.
All he does is a slideshow for math, so you don't actually understand anything from his lectures. Go to the DGDs if you want to pass, and his exams are ridiculously hard.

All he does is click through a slideshow. Mind you, this is linear algebra, not some theory course. Why I do even show up? It's at 8:30am. Just go to the DGDs and you should be okay. Oh and he's not funny at all, and he's really strict. Expect to get -1 marks for being wrong on the midterm, not a regular 0.
He's a very good professor. Knows exactly what he's doing and he teaches it effectively. He can be very strict in the classroom environment. I would definitely recommend him.
He is great at what he does. Just do not talk in his class :D
This professor use powerpoint effectively, and students can get good marks if they practice more and read the power point carefully.

His lectures are long and tedious and he relies strictly on slides which is not always preferable for math based classes.  But, he is helpful and available outside of class hours for students requiring extra help.

he records his lectures so you don't have to go to class, which is thoughtful, but I think you're better off going anyways. He doesn't make you buy the latest version of the book, and even offers a free online book with appropriate exercises. He makes learning very accessible. His slides are really good. great prof.
Great prof. I'd highly recommend him.
amazing problem solving skills!

He is aN OK Prof because he explains things in detail; however, his explanations are extremely technical and not well-suited for first year. His slides are extensive, but he does not variate from them and reads them directly. He has good office hours, but it seems that you are unwelcome if you visit him, such that your presence is a bother to him.
He forgets that he teaches a first year class and makes the material much more difficult to learn than it has to be.
really helpful ppt. both mid-term and assignments are pretty easy...however, the final is little tricky and too much question to be finished in a limit time.
Really nice! Awesome prof. Extremely helpful. Tough course, but if you put in the effort you'll do ok...

Pros: Posts slides containing ALL info and audio of the lecture after the lecture, which is really helpful. His slides really reflect the difficulty that you will be tested on in midterms/exams.  Very easy prof, if you study the slides. Cons: Boring prof.  When people talk in his class, he will slap the desk until it's quiet. Overall: Reccomended.
